description:
FLASH FACT: The war between the Amazons and the Atlantians has arrived. The battle between Diana of Themyscira and Emperor Aquaman will tear this world apart – unless The Flash can fix it!

Summary:

Flashpoint #4 starts in Fawcett City as Eugene, Pedro, Darla, Billy, Mary, Freddie watch the president addresses to the people it was wrong to have hope in the super-humans. The teens argue on what to do next.

In Coast City, Hector Hammond readies a custom F-35 for Hal Jordan. Hector berates Hal for having a smug smile across his face, Hal tells Hector he knows what the stakes are, but he can't focus on the fear or he''ll go hide.

In Metropolis, Batman, Barry and Cyborg try to fend off the security from the Superman facility. Then out of no where Element Woman, Emily Sung douses the security with gas, and she brought extra juice boxes. As this team discuss their next move, Barry is hit with a surge of memories, until Batman gives him an anti-epileptic so it slows down the electrical activity in Barry's brain.

In Fawcett City, Pedro, Billy, Eugene, Mary, Freddie, Darla and Tawny continue to argue their next move. Billy says they need to stop the Atlanteans and the Amazonians. Then Batman, Emily Sung, Cyborg and Barry burst into their home. They ask Billy to help Barry with his mental deterioration. Then Billy sees himself in the other universe, where he saw hope. Then they tune in on the news in which they hear that Hal Jordan has been confirmed as a casualty, and a giant tidal wave has hit the U.K. Then Barry takes Thomas into the kitchen saying they have to stop them. Thomas argues it's all going to be wiped away, Barry contests he could forget everything and they could fail to stop Thawne, and if they do they will have to be stuck in this world. Thomas says either we change this world or we let it burn in hell. Flash tells Cyborg to round up the resistance, and the kids decide to join. Batman just stands there, until Flash remarks "Bruce would've come." Thomas then decides to join.

In New Themyscira, Element Woman, Flash, the Shazam kids, are all in Thomas' jet. As Aquaman and Wonder Woman fight, the kids turn into Shazam. Captain Thunder attacks Wonder Woman. Flash tries to reason with Aquaman, then the Enchantress betrays everyone by splitting the kids from Captain Thunder. Wonder Woman notes he's just a boy but goes on and kills him. Then Thawne comes back and taunts Barry on what he did.
name: Flashpoint: Chapter Four of Five

description: In a very ordinary  building Roxy and Angela , two twin sisters, seem to be the only ones to realize the brutal killing of their roommates , for which  it seems to be no evidence. Dylan 's up to investigate and find out what horror lurks within the walls of the dilapidated building.
name: Discesa nell'abisso

description:
Dylan is called to investigate a murder , it seems, by a werewolf . To solve the mystery he has available the same day , several times . It seems that the time for him can no longer slide normally.

The story is based on "Groundhog Day", a 1993 action movie.
name: Il giorno del licantropo

description: Why Adam Douglas claims to have been on the moon? The official story does not include his name, but his daughter Selina is now convinced of the contrary. So what happened during that mysterious mission that now, years later, returns to chase Adam?
name: Il tredicesimo uomo

description: Oddities and mysterious characters from Victorian era invade London and vice versa. Panic and fear spread in the city and Dylan , intent on saving a sweet and forlorn maiden , must find a way to solve the temporal disaster just unleashed .
name: Fuga dal passato

description: Dylan is trapped in a tunnel after a train accident along with the other survivors of the disaster . In front of hunger and thirst, Dylan will have to face the monster of the struggle for survival , able to unleash the most brutal instincts of the human soul .
name: Seppelliti vivi!

description: In Plymouth , since the naval museum has purchased and restored the Sovereign , an old sailing ship, brutal murders are occurring . The museum director is concerned that to take disaster was the ship with its ancient curse. Dylan 's up to shed light on the mysterious affair .
name: La strage dei Graham

description: The mysterious discovery of a devil in formaldehyde in a jar . A series of murders . Dylan Dog must stop the terrible demon Xiphenor before the world is destroyed by the darkness .
name: Il piccolo diavolo

description: Violent and insane murders are upsetting the chemistry department of Professor Skinner . The man becomes the first suspect of Rose, a researcher of the department, because of the hate and resentment that his figure emanates to the students . Dylan will help the young researcher to understand what's happening in the University .
name: Il re delle mosche

description: Stella Stevens , charming and icy girl, turns to Martin in tears to find out the truth about the mysterious death of his dog, the only living being loved by her . Their search leads them in various stages , up to a temple in the Sinai Peninsula , where a terrible conspiracy is underway .
name: Polvere d'oro

description: Angie and Diana are team again , this time to save the kingdom of Faeries from the Dark Lord.
name: Spade, sfide e magie

description: SURPRISE ISSUE! Well, if we told you what it was, it wouldn't be a surprise, would it? Here's a hint: there will be blood! Now there's a first for an issue of Glamourpuss. 'The History of Photorealism' section continues with the events of September 6, 1956 and the death of Rip Kirby creator, Alex Raymond.
Fred Van Lente's follow-up to his 2-issue mini-series published by Image, again featuring his mobsters with super-powers.
name: The Silencers

description: The mystery of Angie's death is still unsolved and detectives Packard and Craft have come to Eric for questioning. After an unproductive interview, the detectives leave his home very suspicious. Eric decides to pursue them and send 'em a message.

description:
There are innumerable and varying potential futures awaiting mankind. Among them exists only one constant: the rise of the Deathloks! Seeded in our present they grow, a time virus spreading across all possibilities, infiltrating the fate of mankind. One thing stands in their way: a man who shouldn't exist.

They come in waves, an army of time-displaced Deathlok troopers forged from Earth's greatest warriors - Captain America, Spider-Man, Elektra, Cyclops, Venom, the Thing, Bullseye - all soldiers in the army of Deathlok. All operating under one directive: Fantomex must die!

Plus: When a situation calls for hard choices, the Uncanny X-Force is there to step in. Lady Deathstrike, with the deadly Reavers at her side, set out to destroy the X-Men in their home! Deathstrike will obliterate the X-Men or die trying, and this new X-Force is more than happy to oblige. As the line between right and wrong become more and more blurred, will the X-Force be heralded as heroes - or villains?

Collecting UNCANNY X-FORCE #5-7 and #5.1, and Deathlok's first appearance from 1974's ASTONISHING TALES #25.
name: Uncanny X-Force: Deathlok Nation

description: There can only be one Queen! Following the explosive events against President Obama in BOMB QUEEN, VOL. 6, Bomb Queen continues her war against the world when she travels to London to kill the Queen of England. But Madame Queen has a few super heroine tricks up her sleeve, too...
name: One-Shot
